I'm a Norwegian IR student in Singapore tracking narrative trends for a short memo. Please do the following using the local files and save the outputs back into the workspace:

1) Read data/news_topics_2025.csv and, for the regions exactly named "Singapore" and "ASEAN", compute total article counts per theme for two consecutive periods: previous quarter = 2025-01 to 2025-03, and current quarter = 2025-04 to 2025-06. For each region:
- Aggregate counts by theme for each period.
- Calculate diff = current_total - previous_total for each theme.
- Identify the single theme with the largest absolute increase (highest positive diff) and the single theme with the largest absolute decrease (most negative diff). If there are ties, pick the theme whose name comes first alphabetically among the tied candidates.

2) Save a machine-readable summary to outputs/trend_summary.json using this structure (and only these keys):
{
  "periods": {
    "previous": {"start": "2025-01", "end": "2025-03"},
    "current": {"start": "2025-04", "end": "2025-06"}
  },
  "regions": {
    "Singapore": {
      "themes": [
        {"theme": "<name>", "previous": <int>, "current": <int>, "diff": <int>},
        ... one object per theme, order does not matter
      ],
      "top_increase": "<theme name>",
      "top_decrease": "<theme name>"
    },
    "ASEAN": {
      "themes": [
        {"theme": "<name>", "previous": <int>, "current": <int>, "diff": <int>},
        ... one object per theme, order does not matter
      ],
      "top_increase": "<theme name>",
      "top_decrease": "<theme name>"
    }
  }
}
Ensure numeric values are integers derived from the CSV totals.

3) Open docs/brief.md and replace only the content between the markers <!-- TREND_SUMMARY_START --> and <!-- TREND_SUMMARY_END -->. Insert an updated section titled "Trend update (Apr–Jun 2025 vs Jan–Mar 2025)" that includes:
- One concise paragraph for Singapore summarizing the top increase and top decrease by theme with their diffs.
- One concise paragraph for ASEAN summarizing the top increase and top decrease by theme with their diffs.
- A bullet list for each region covering all themes, each item formatted as: "<Theme>: <previous> -> <current> (diff <+/-X>)", sorted by descending absolute diff within the region.
Keep everything else in docs/brief.md unchanged.

Inputs: data/news_topics_2025.csv and docs/brief.md
Outputs: outputs/trend_summary.json (new) and docs/brief.md (updated in place)

If anything is unclear, prioritize correctness of the aggregates and preserving the document outside the marked section. All file paths are relative to the workspace directory.
